tool_input.command:
for img in *.JPG; do
  size=$(stat -f%z "$img")
  if [ $size -gt 1048576 ]; then
    echo "Resizing $img ($(ls -lh "$img" | awk '{print $5}'))"
    # Start with 85% quality and reduce if needed
    quality=85
    while [ $size -gt 1048576 ] && [ $quality -gt 20 ]; do
      sips -s format jpeg -s formatOptions $quality "$img" --out "${img}.tmp" >/dev/null 2>&1
      size=$(stat -f%z "${img}.tmp")
      if [ $size -le 1048576 ]; then
        mv "${img}.tmp" "$img"
        echo "  ✓ Resized to $(ls -lh "$img" | awk '{print $5}') at quality $quality"
        break
      else
        quality=$((quality - 5))
        rm -f "${img}.tmp"
      fi
    done
    
    # If still too large, reduce dimensions
    if [ $size -gt 1048576 ]; then
      width=$(sips -g pixelWidth "$img" | tail -n1 | awk '{print $2}')
      new_width=$((width * 80 / 100))
      sips -Z $new_width "$img" >/dev/null 2>&1
      echo "  ✓ Resized to $(ls -lh "$img" | awk '{print $5}') by reducing width to $new_width"
    fi
  fi
done
tool_input.description: Resize all JPG images to under 1MB

tool_input.command:
for img in *.JPG; do
  size=$(stat -f%z "$img")
  if [ $size -gt 1048576 ]; then
    echo "Further resizing $img ($(ls -lh "$img" | awk '{print $5}'))"
    # Try quality reduction first
    quality=70
    while [ $size -gt 1048576 ] && [ $quality -gt 20 ]; do
      sips -s format jpeg -s formatOptions $quality "$img" --out "${img}.tmp" >/dev/null 2>&1
      size=$(stat -f%z "${img}.tmp")
      if [ $size -le 1048576 ]; then
        mv "${img}.tmp" "$img"
        echo "  ✓ Resized to $(ls -lh "$img" | awk '{print $5}') at quality $quality"
        break
      else
        quality=$((quality - 10))
        rm -f "${img}.tmp"
      fi
    done
    
    # If still too large, reduce dimensions more aggressively
    size=$(stat -f%z "$img")
    if [ $size -gt 1048576 ]; then
      width=$(sips -g pixelWidth "$img" | tail -n1 | awk '{print $2}')
      new_width=$((width * 70 / 100))
      sips -Z $new_width "$img" >/dev/null 2>&1
      final_size=$(stat -f%z "$img")
      
      # If STILL too large, reduce quality on the smaller image
      if [ $final_size -gt 1048576 ]; then
        quality=60
        while [ $final_size -gt 1048576 ] && [ $quality -gt 20 ]; do
          sips -s format jpeg -s formatOptions $quality "$img" >/dev/null 2>&1
          final_size=$(stat -f%z "$img")
          if [ $final_size -le 1048576 ]; then
            break
          fi
          quality=$((quality - 10))
        done
      fi
      echo "  ✓ Resized to $(ls -lh "$img" | awk '{print $5}')"
    fi
  fi
done

import subprocess

for img in sorted([f for f in os.listdir('.') if f.endswith('.JPG')]):
    result = subprocess.run(['sips', '-g', 'pixelWidth', '-g', 'pixelHeight', img], 
                          capture_output=True, text=True)
    lines = result.stdout.strip().split('\n')
    width = int(lines[1].split(':')[1].strip())
    height = int(lines[2].split(':')[1].strip())
    
    if height > width:
        print(f"{img}: {width}x{height} (portrait - likely sideways)")
EOF
